egismoc: add Egis ETU906 (1c7a:05a5) for Samsung Galaxy Book5

SPDX-License-Identifier: LGPL-2.1-or-later
(derives from libfprint egismoc.c, LGPL-2.1-or-later)

The Samsung Galaxy Book5 (960XHA / board NP964XHA-KG2DE) ships an Egis
Technology (LighTuning) ETU906Axx-E Match-on-Chip fingerprint reader with
USB id 1c7a:05a5, which is not present in the egismoc id_table.

The device speaks the egismoc "type 2" check-prefix protocol (like its
1c7a:05a1 sibling) and enrolls in 15 stages.

IMPORTANT - SDCP REQUIRED:
  This id_table line alone is sufficient for *detection* (fprintd-list) but
  NOT for enrollment. The ETU906 requires the SDCP secure handshake. Mainline
  libfprint's egismoc driver derives from FP_TYPE_DEVICE and does not perform
  SDCP, so enroll/verify fail with "Unrecognized response from device" or
  enroll-disconnected.

  For a WORKING enroll/verify, build the SDCP-capable egismoc fork, which
  derives the driver from FPI_TYPE_SDCP_DEVICE and already carries this exact
  id_table entry (with EGISMOC_DRIVER_MAX_ENROLL_STAGES_15):

      https://github.com/TenSeventy7/libfprint-egismoc-sdcp

  On mainline this patch yields detection only.

diff --git a/libfprint/drivers/egismoc/egismoc.c b/libfprint/drivers/egismoc/egismoc.c
--- a/libfprint/drivers/egismoc/egismoc.c
+++ b/libfprint/drivers/egismoc/egismoc.c
@@ -57,6 +57,7 @@ static const FpIdEntry egismoc_id_table[] = {
   { .vid = 0x1c7a, .pid = 0x0587, .driver_data = EGISMOC_DRIVER_CHECK_PREFIX_TYPE1 | EGISMOC_DRIVER_MAX_ENROLL_STAGES_20 },
   { .vid = 0x1c7a, .pid = 0x0588, .driver_data = EGISMOC_DRIVER_CHECK_PREFIX_TYPE1 | EGISMOC_DRIVER_MAX_ENROLL_STAGES_20 },
   { .vid = 0x1c7a, .pid = 0x05a1, .driver_data = EGISMOC_DRIVER_CHECK_PREFIX_TYPE2 },
+  { .vid = 0x1c7a, .pid = 0x05a5, .driver_data = EGISMOC_DRIVER_CHECK_PREFIX_TYPE2 },
   { .vid = 0,      .pid = 0,      .driver_data = 0 }
 };
